2. Feature Scaling (Standardization)

Many ML algorithms work better when features have similar scales.

Standardization converts data into Z-Scores.

Examples:

Height
Salary
Age

After standardization:

Mean = 0
Standard Deviation = 1

Algorithms like:

Logistic Regression
SVM
KNN
PCA
Neural Networks

perform better after standardization.

3. Compare Different Distributions

Suppose:

Student A

Maths = 90
Mean = 80
SD = 5

Student B

Physics = 85
Mean = 70
SD = 10

Instead of comparing raw marks, compare their Z-Scores.

The student with the higher Z-Score performed better relative to their class.

Properties of Z-Score
Mean becomes 0
Standard Deviation becomes 1
Unitless value
Can be positive or negative
Used for standardization and outlier detection
