Interview Questions
1. What is a Z-Score?

A Z-Score measures how many standard deviations a data point is from the mean.

2. What does a negative Z-Score mean?

The value lies below the mean.

3. What does a positive Z-Score mean?

The value lies above the mean.

4. When is Z-Score used?
Outlier detection
Data standardization
Comparing values from different datasets
Machine Learning preprocessing
5. What is considered an outlier using Z-Score?

Generally:

Z > 3
